// MsgRejectRecovery records one guardian's rejection of an open SOCIAL request. Membership is proven
// exactly as MsgApproveRecovery proves it — by OPENING the commitment with (guardian_did, salt) — and
// the same eligibility rules apply: the revealed guardian must be an ACTIVE DID and the signer must
// control it.
//
// On reaching the DID's guardian threshold the request becomes REJECTED and its deposit is forfeited to
// the fee collector, freeing the slot. This is what makes the per-DID slot cap unexhaustible: a griefer
// who fills every slot with spurious requests can be cleared by the guardians instead of the DID being
// blocked until TTL — and the users that would lock out are exactly the lost-key owners recovery exists
// to serve.
//
